112‚Üí**`src/lib/stores/chart-store.ts`**
113‚Üí```typescript
114‚Üíimport { atom } from 'nanostores';
115‚Üíimport type { ChartPoint } from '../types';
116‚Üí
117‚Üíexport const chartStore = atom<ChartPoint[]>([]);
118‚Üí```
119‚Üí
120‚Üí**Key rules:**
121‚Üí- Import `atom` from `'nanostores'` (NOT `@nanostores/core` or any other path)
122‚Üí- Import types using `import type` syntax
123‚Üí- Use relative path `'../types'` (stores are in `src/lib/stores/`, types is at `src/lib/types.ts`)
124‚Üí- Always use explicit generic on `atom<T>()` -- never let TypeScript infer the type
125‚Üí- `null` initial value for stores that have no data yet (price, market); empty array for chart; `'connecting'` as meaningful default for status
126‚Üí- One store per file, one export per file
127‚Üí- No barrel file (`stores/index.ts`) -- consumers import directly from each store file
