352‚Üí### Import Patterns
353‚Üí
354‚ÜíComponents and services will import stores and formatters as follows (for reference in future stories):
355‚Üí
356‚Üí```typescript
357‚Üí// Store imports (from a component or service)
358‚Üíimport { priceStore } from '../lib/stores/price-store';
359‚Üíimport { statusStore } from '../lib/stores/status-store';
360‚Üíimport { marketStore } from '../lib/stores/market-store';
361‚Üíimport { chartStore } from '../lib/stores/chart-store';
362‚Üí
363‚Üí// Formatter imports (from a component)
364‚Üíimport { formatPrice, formatPercent, formatAbsoluteChange } from '../lib/utils/format-utils';
365‚Üí
366‚Üí// Type imports
367‚Üíimport type { PriceTick } from '../lib/types';
368‚Üí```
369‚Üí
370‚Üí### Anti-Patterns (DO NOT)
371‚Üí
372‚Üí- **No barrel files** -- do NOT create `src/lib/stores/index.ts` or `src/lib/utils/index.ts`. Import directly from each module.
373‚Üí- **No setInterval** -- not relevant to this story, but never use it in the project. Use recursive `setTimeout` for polling.
374‚Üí- **No store writes from components** -- stores are written to ONLY by services (Story 2.2+). This story only creates stores; writing happens in later stories.
375‚Üí- **No manual string formatting** -- never use `toFixed()`, string concatenation, or template literals to format numbers for display. Always use `Intl.NumberFormat`.
376‚Üí- **No derived data in stores** -- do not store formatted strings. Stores hold raw numbers; formatting happens at the component level via `format-utils.ts`.
377‚Üí- **No default objects as initial store values** -- use `null` for "no data yet" (not `{ price: 0, timestamp: 0, direction: 'neutral' }`).
