### Accessibility

- **`<div role="status" aria-live="polite">`**: The outer wrapper has `role="status"` which implies `aria-live="polite"`. Screen readers will announce changes to the text content when the status changes. The `polite` setting means announcements wait until the screen reader finishes current speech.
- **Status text updates**: When `statusStore` changes, the text content updates (e.g., from "Live" to "Reconnecting..."). Screen readers announce this change automatically because of `aria-live="polite"`.
- **Stale badge on PriceCard**: Uses `role="status"` so screen readers also announce when data becomes stale.
- **No color-only communication**: The status text ("Live", "Reconnecting...", "Connection lost", "Live -- CoinCap") provides meaning beyond just the dot color.

### Animation Timing Summary

| Animation | Duration | Easing | Trigger |
|---|---|---|---|
| Reconnecting dot pulse | 1.5s | ease-in-out | `statusStore` = `'reconnecting'` |
| State transition (dot color) | 300ms | ease-in-out | Any `statusStore` change |
| State transition (text) | 300ms | ease-in-out | Any `statusStore` change |
| Stale badge fade-in | 300ms | ease-out | `statusStore` = `'stale'` |
| Stale badge fade-out | 300ms | ease-out | `statusStore` leaves `'stale'` |

All animations disabled (0ms) when `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` is active.

### Anti-Patterns (DO NOT)

- **Never** call `statusStore.set()` from StatusIndicator or PriceCard. Only services (ConnectionManager) write to statusStore.
- **Never** import `connection-manager.ts` directly from a component. All state comes through stores.
- **Never** use JavaScript `setTimeout` for animation timing. CSS transitions and `@keyframes` handle all visual timing.
- **Never** use toast notifications or modals for connection state changes. The subtle indicator is the only UI.
- **Never** hide or replace the price value when stale. The stale badge is additive.
- **Never** use `setInterval` or JavaScript animation loops for the pulse. CSS `@keyframes` with `animation` property handles this.
- **Never** show alarming error states. The status indicator is intentionally quiet and subtle.
- **Never** add a UI framework. This island uses vanilla TypeScript DOM manipulation.
- **Never** create barrel files. Import directly from specific modules.

